parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, tachometer, and other gauges to malfunction, leading to a safety hazard as the driver is unable to accurately determine the vehicle's speed.
symptoms: Speedometer readings are erratic or stuck
tachometer readings are low or stuck
other gauges (e.g.
oil
fuel
temperature) malfunction or are stuck
and the cluster may display incorrect or misleading information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated seat can cause a distraction to the driver, leading to a potential safety hazard.
symptoms: Heated seat turns on and off randomly
heated seat stays on constantly
and the controls for the heated seat do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause a short circuit, leading to a potential fire hazard.
symptoms: Corroded or burnt wiring
melted insulation
and faulty connections in the wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear indicator can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's gear, leading to a potential safety hazard.
symptoms: The gear indicator is difficult or impossible to read
especially during daylight hours.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a variety of malfunctions, leading to a potential safety hazard.
symptoms: The blower motor runs continuously with the ignition off
the battery discharges with the ignition off
and there is a burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the loss of braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brake pedal travels to the floor
loss of braking power
brake fluid leak
rust or corrosion on brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and Stabilitrak system can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: ABS and Stabilitrak warning lights illuminate
loss of traction
sudden acceleration or deceleration
loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause loss of braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels to the floor
loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle will not move from 2nd to 3rd gear
the transmission hot light comes on
the vehicle loses forward momentum
the transmission engages into 4W LO while driving on the freeway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Drive shaft failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The drive shaft breaks
the vehicle makes a loud noise
the vehicle shakes and vibrates
the vehicle will not move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and hydraulic system failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gear status indicator failure can cause the driver to be unaware of the gear the vehicle is in, increasing the chances of crashing.
symptoms: The gear status indicator does not display the selected gear
the shift lever position indicator does not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Differential failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a whining noise
the differential has a mechanical issue
the ring inside the differential is bad.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Speedometer failure can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's speed, increasing the chances of crashing.
symptoms: The speedometer is stuck at 120 mph
the speedometer does not display the correct speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Four-wheel drive system failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle engages into 4W LO while driving on the freeway
the vehicle rolls back if the brakes are not applied.
